      "content": "That makes sense. So, if we follow that logic, wouldn't any rule—even ones meant to stop things like misinformation or hate speech—be inherently illegitimate because they bypass those natural rights? Like, shouldn't the \"truth\" be determined by the people online rather than by some government agency acting as an arbiter?",
